<br />I update scroll registers every frame, so that the screen doesn't risk to shake or anything like this. This doesn't cause any visual problems. I update sprites only when they are ready. Anyway, in 99% of the case your game loop should complete within a frame, else your game will be buggy anyway. It's just good to design it so that it still look alright when it slows down.</div>

